<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/565005084/2025-26/evaluation> a ns1:EvaluationSystem ;
    ns1:evaluationDescription """PROGRESSIVE ASSESSMENT:
The assessment consists of three parts:

1) Public presentation and defense of the assigned work.
* This involves a public presentation and defense in English of a recent research article selected and provided by the faculty. Reproduction of the fundamental results is required, and clarity in oral presentation, appropriate use of scientific language, and analysis and discussion of the results will be positively evaluated.
* This component is mandatory, has a minimum grade of 4 out of 10 points, and constitutes 40% of the final grade.

2) Submission of the project report.
* The report should be of appropriate length and written in English. Evaluation criteria will include the format used, presentation of information, written expression in English, analysis, and discussion of results, among other factors.
* This component is mandatory, has a minimum grade of 4 out of 10 points, and constitutes 30% of the final grade.

3) Submission of computational codes.
* The scripts and codes used to reproduce the results of the presented article must be deposited in a public repository (e.g., GitHub). Evaluation will consider the documentation of the repository (e.g., a clear project description and usage instructions in the README file), organization of contents/files (e.g., using different folders), and code clarity (e.g., commenting and documenting), among other aspects.
* This component is mandatory, has a minimum grade of 4 out of 10 points, and constitutes 30% of the final grade.
The course is passed if, after meeting all the minimum requirements of the progressive assessment, the final score is equal to or greater than 5.

REGULAR EXAMINATION
* Students who fail the progressive assessment may take a comprehensive examination for the course during the regular examination period.
* The examination will consist of the same parts as the progressive assessment, subject to the same requirements and weightings, with the final grade being calculated based on these weightings.

* The three parts of the progressive assessment can be completed individually or in groups of up to two people.

* The course is passed if the result of the examination is equal to or greater than 5.

EXTRAORDINARY EXAMINATION
* Students who fail the course during the regular examination period may take a comprehensive examination during the extraordinary examination period.
* The examination will consist of the same parts as the progressive assessment, subject to the same requirements and weightings, with the final grade being calculated based on these weightings.
* The three parts of the extraordinary examination assessment must be completed individually.
* The course is passed if the result of the comprehensive extraordinary examination is equal to or greater than 5.
* The course is passed if, after meeting all the minimum requirements of the progressive assessment, the final score is equal to or greater than 5."""@es ;
